#### Summary of the scheme (WWF)

The WWF's hierarchical classification system organizes life on Earth as follows:

*   **[Biosphere](/Biosphere)**
    *   **[Biogeographic realms](/Biogeographic_realm)** (terrestrial) (8 realms)
        *   **[Ecoregions](/Ecoregion)** (867 ecoregions), each characterized by a biome, a major habitat type (14 types)
            *   **[Ecosystems](/Ecosystems)** (also referred to as [biotopes](/Biotope))
    *   **[Biosphere](/Biosphere)**
        *   **[Biogeographic realms](/Biogeographic_realm)** (freshwater) (8 realms)
            *   **[Ecoregions](/Ecoregions)** (426 ecoregions), each characterized by a biome, a major habitat type (12 types)
                *   **[Ecosystems](/Ecosystems)** (biotopes)
    *   **[Biosphere](/Biosphere)**
        *   **Biogeographic realms** (marine) (12 realms)
            *   **([Marine provinces](/Ecoregion))** (62 provinces)
                *   **[Ecoregions](/Ecoregions)** (232 ecoregions), each characterized by a biome, a major habitat type (5 types)
                    *   **[Ecosystems](/Ecosystems)** (biotopes)

